# Subagent Maintenance

## Purpose

Use this checklist whenever you add, rename, remove, or materially change a subagent.

## Gate

- First confirm that no existing specialist fits the work.
- Missing specialist coverage is a stop condition, not permission for the orchestrator to keep the task.
- Default **`model`** for a new role card is **`inherit`** unless a stronger lane is explicitly justified.

## Required update surfaces

1. Add or update the role card in `.cursor/agents/`
2. Update `docs/AGENT_REGISTRY.mdc`
3. Update **`.cursor/rules/`** when behavior is global (`global/`) or engineering-wide (`engineering/`); add a focused rule file rather than growing unrelated rules
4. Add or update **`.cursor/skills/<domain>/<skill-name>/SKILL.md`** when reusable execution steps are needed
5. Update `docs/AGENT_ORCHESTRATION.mdc` if authority or handoff behavior changes
6. Update `docs/MODEL_ROUTING.mdc` if default model pinning changes
7. Update `AGENTS.mdc` if the repo-level operating contract changes
8. If the lane owns product briefs, confirm canonical **`docs/`** + **`product/README.md`** stay accurate
9. Record the change in `docs/DECISION_LOG.mdc` if it affects governance
10. Update `docs/HYGIENE.mdc` if the lane affects cleanup or removal policy
11. Update `README.md` only if the top-level operating stance changes
12. If you are recording formal workflow validation evidence, append to `docs/research-workbench-validation.md` and/or `docs/DECISION_LOG.mdc`

## Add-a-subagent checklist

- define the mission clearly
- define inputs
- define output contract
- define stop conditions
- set **`model: inherit`** unless there is an explicit reason to pin a model
- document any non-default model choice in the role card and `docs/MODEL_ROUTING.mdc`
- ensure packet usage is still valid
- note whether the subagent changes the visual or documentation system
- update `docs/AGENT_REGISTRY.mdc` and evidence surfaces when the lane becomes part of the official set

## Remove-or-merge checklist

- remove stale references from docs and rules
- confirm no skills still point at the old role
- note the reason in `docs/DECISION_LOG.mdc`
